        The ketogenic diet, commonly known as the keto diet, is a high-fat, low-carbohydrate eating plan designed to induce a metabolic state called ketosis. In ketosis, the body primarily burns fat for fuel instead of carbohydrates. This diet typically involves consuming foods rich in healthy fats, such as avocados, nuts, seeds, and oils, while minimizing the intake of carbohydrates from sources like grains, sugars, and starchy vegetables. By drastically reducing carbohydrate intake, the body shifts its metabolism to use fat as its primary energy source, leading to potential benefits such as weight loss, improved blood sugar control, and enhanced mental clarity. However, the keto diet may not be suitable for everyone, and it&#39;s essential to consult with a healthcare professional before starting any new diet plan.</p>
   
    


